subSubSection.paragraph:
It is allied to 
Orthogonius politior
sp. n., but its clypeus bisetose (quadrisetose in 
Orthogonius politior
), prosternal process well-bordered at apex (unbordered in 
Orthogonius politior
), and the apical lamella of aedeagus shorter and broad at apex (longer and narrow in 
Orthogonius politior
).
